BT 0 g /F2 15 Tf 212.4 750 Td (UNDERSTANDING ANGER IN DBT) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 50 740 m 562 740 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 715 Td (DBT \(Dialectical Behavior Therapy\) views anger as a valid emotion) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 698 Td (that becomes problematic when it leads to destructive behavior.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 681 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 664 Td (THE DBT PERSPECTIVE ON ANGER:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 647 Td (- Anger is not 'bad' - it carries information) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 630 Td (- The problem is not the emotion but the behavioral response) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 613 Td (- You can feel intensely angry AND choose skillful behavior) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 596 Td (- Both things are true: your anger is valid AND your actions matter) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 579 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 562 Td (THE FOUR DBT SKILL MODULES FOR ANGER:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 545 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 528 Td (1. MINDFULNESS - Observing anger without being controlled by it) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 511 Td (   Noticing urges without acting on them) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 494 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 477 Td (2. DISTRESS TOLERANCE - Surviving anger crises without making) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 460 Td (   things worse \(when you can't fix the situation right now\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 443 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 426 Td (3. EMOTION REGULATION - Reducing vulnerability to anger and) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 409 Td (   changing unwanted emotional responses) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 392 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 375 Td (4. INTERPERSONAL EFFECTIVENESS - Expressing anger in ways) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 358 Td (   that maintain relationships and self-respect) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 341 Td () Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 324 Td (WHY ANGER IS ESPECIALLY CHALLENGING:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 307 Td (- Anger feels justified \(so we resist changing it\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 290 Td (- Anger provides temporary power/control) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 273 Td (- Anger masks vulnerable emotions \(hurt, fear, shame\)) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 256 Td (- Anger creates short-term relief but long-term damage) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10.5 Tf 50 239 Td (- Others may reinforce our anger \(agree we're 'right'\)) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
